Change the final three paragraphs, including the lettered list, in 6.2.1.3.2 as follows:

The transmission status parameter will be-is used to pass status information back to the local requesting LLC sublayer entity. IEEE 802.11 specifies the following values for transmission status:

Successful;

Undeliverable (for unacknowledged directed MSDUs when the adotll ShortRetryLimitMax or adotllLongRetryLimitMax retry limit would otherwise be exceeded);

Undeliverable (excessive data length);

Undeliverable (non-null source routing);

Undeliverable: unsupported priority (for priorities other than Contention or ContentionFree_ at an nOSTA; or for priorities other than Contention, ContentionFree, or an integer between and including O and 15 at a QSTA);

Undeliverable: unsupported service class (for service classes other than Reorderable Multicast or Strictly Ordered) for nOSTAs and service classes other than QoSAck or QoSNoAck for OSTAs);

Unavailable priority (for ContentionFree when no PC or HC is available, or an integer between and including 1 and 15 at a OSTA that is associated in an nQBSS, or an integer between and including 8 and 15 at a OSTA that is a member of an IBSS, in which case the MSDU is transmitted with a provided priority of Contention);

Undeliverable: unavailable service class (for Strictly Ordered service when the STA's power management mode is other than "active" for nQSTAs; QSTAs do not return this value as they do not provide the StrictlyOrdered service);

Undeliverable (TransmitMSDUTimer reached adotl 1MaxTransmitMSDULifetime before successful delivery;

Undeliverable (no BSS available);

Undeliverable (cannot encrypt with a null key);

Undeliverable (MSDU transmit timer reached the value in dotlIEDCATableMSDULifetime or dot| 1QAPEDCATableMSDULifetime prior to a successful delivery or the TransmitMSDUTimer reached the delay bound prior to successful delivery;

Undeliverable (Block Ack timeout value has been exceeded).

The provided priority parameter specifies the priority that was used for the associated data unit transfer (Contention, or ContentionFree, or an integer between and including 0 and 15).

The provided service class parameter specifies the class of service used for the associated data unit transfer. In nOSTAs, the value of this parameter is fReorderableMulticast or Strictly Ordered). In QSTAs, it is RoSAck or QoSNoAck.

End of changes to Clause 6.

